com.storytron.uber

Class Deikto

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.storytron.uber.Deikto
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable

    public final class Deikto
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable
    This class is the root of the world model.

    A world model is a set of verbs, actors, stages, things and traits that describe the universe where stories evolve using Storyteller. The world model is implemented by the set of classes in the package com.storytron.uber.

    The world model also contains its own dictionary of operators. This dictionary contains many operators common to all the storyworlds, plus some specific operators that only apply to it (most likely comming from custom traits).

    This class enforces global limits on the model to prevent arbitrarily huge storyworlds. For that sake, most of the model parts that are in low levels of the hierarchy, like Roles and Role.Options, are added and removed through methods in this class. The only exception when enforcing limits are the script nodes, which global counts must be updated by the editors that manipulate the scripts.

    Deikto provides also some auxiliary functionality:

    • loading the model from a stream
      • #Deikto(InputStream, File)
      A mechanism is provided to load old storyworld formats through DeiktoLoader.
    • saving the model to a stream
      • writeXML(OutputStream)
    • providing the path to resource images
      • getImageFile(String)
    • saving images associated to the model in a directory on disk
      • writeResources(File)
    • collects and provides background information about various parts of the model
      • #getPeople(boolean)
      • #getPlaces(boolean)
      • #getThings(boolean)
    • traversals over Scripts
      • traverseScripts(com.storytron.uber.Deikto.ScriptTraverser)
      • traverseScripts(com.storytron.uber.Script.NodeTraverser)
    • cloning the non-fixed parts of the model
      • cloneWorldShareLanguage())

    First level of world models

    Each model has some fixed sets:
    • a set of verbs (verbs)
    • a set of actor traits (getActorTraits())
    • a set of stage traits (getStageTraits())
    • a set of prop traits (getPropTraits())
    • a set of actor text traits (getTextTraits(TraitType))
    • a set of stage text traits (getTextTraits(TraitType))
    • a set of prop text traits (getTextTraits(TraitType))
    We say that these sets are fixed because they are not modified during execution of a story, neither any of their elements.

    And each model has some non-fixed sets:

    • a set of Actors (actors)
    • a set of Stages (stages)
    • a set of Props (props)
    Elements are not added or deleted from these sets, but certain values of them can be modified during execution of a story.

    All the elements on these sets have associated indexes, the indexes can be used for fast lookups. It is possible to insert elements at specific indexes or change the indexes if needed. The operations that involve removing or adding elements are implemented in Deikto.

    Traits also have a rename operation because renaming a trait requires renaming some other elements associated to it.

      • version

        public int version
        This version number helps differentiate different copies of a storyworld.

        Whenever changes are made to a storyworld, the version number is incremented once (and only once) until the storyworld is saved. If after saving a storyworld, new changes are done, then the version number is incremented again.

        The Swat.UndoManager class is responsible for updating the version number. This is convenient because the UndoManager keeps track of all the possible changes that can be done to a storyworld, and has knowledge to determine if modifications are changes being undone or new changes.

        Builds a Deikto instance from a storyworld data saved somewhere else. The data to read can be in any version of the format, provided that DeiktoLoader knows how to transform it to the most up to date format.
        Parameters:
        isXML - input stream to read storyworld data from.
        f - file path used to locate images associated to the storyworld. It is intended to hold the name of the storyworld file on disk, the images are expected to be in a directory next to it. The name of the file is used by storyteller to identify if saved stories belong to this storyworld.

        Creates a trait of type tt with name traitLabel and inserts it at index i (the index is given wrt the trait list containing the traits of the given type). Make sure that there does not exist a trait with the same name, and that it name is distinct from the name of an existing operator.

        This method creates the trait and the operators (see addTrait(com.storytron.uber.Deikto.TraitType, int, FloatTrait) for details) for getting and setting the trait.

        Parameters:
        visible - tells if the trait is visible or not.
        Throws:
        LimitException

      • addTrait

        public void addTrait(Deikto.TraitType tt,
                     int i,
                     FloatTrait t)
              throws LimitException
        Add a FloatTrait to the world. This method creates the Operators for getting and setting the trait. All of the generated operators are created by OperatorFactory class. Make sure that there does not exist a trait with the same name, even if it is of different type.

        The following operators are common to all traits:

        • TraitName: returns the trait value for a given element.
        • SetTraitName: Sets the value of a trait for a given element.
        • PTraitName: returns the perceived trait value of one actor for another.
        • CTraitName: returns the confidence in the perceived trait value of one actor for another.
        • SetPTraitName: Sets the perceived trait value of one actor for another.
        • SetCTraitName: Sets the confidence in the perceived trait value of one actor for another.
        • TraitNameWeight: returns the trait weight value for a given actor.
        • PTraitNameWeight: returns the perceived trait weight value from one actor towards another.

        Parameters:
        i - the index where to insert the Trait in the collection for traits of type tt.
        Throws:
        LimitException

      • traverseScripts

        public void traverseScripts(Deikto.ScriptTraverser t)

        Traverses each script in the world model using the traverser t. Use it like this: 

                dk.traverse(new Traverser(){
                public boolean traversing(Script s) {
          do something with s
          return true;
        }
        });
        Here "do something with s" will be executed for each script in the world model.

      • traverseScriptsJustOnce

        public void traverseScriptsJustOnce(Deikto.ScriptTraverser t)
        Same as traverseScripts(ScriptTraverser) but shared scripts are traversed only once.

      • traverseScripts

        public void traverseScripts(Verb zVerb,
                            Deikto.ScriptTraverser t)
        Same as traverseScripts(ScriptTraverser) but searches only over a given verb.

      • traverseScripts

        public void traverseScripts(Verb zVerb,
                            Role.Link zRole,
                            Deikto.ScriptTraverser t)
        Same as traverseScripts(ScriptTraverser) but searches only over a given role.

      • traverseScripts

        public void traverseScripts(Script.NodeTraverser t)

        Traverses each node of each script in the world model using the traverser t. Use it like this: 

                dk.traverse(new Script.Traverser(){
                public boolean traversing(Script s, DMTN n) {
          do something with s and n
          return true;
        }
        });
        Here "do something with s and n" will be executed for each node in each script in the world model (see Script#traverse(ScriptTraverser)).

      • traverseScriptsJustOnce

        public void traverseScriptsJustOnce(Script.NodeTraverser t)
        Same as traverseScriptsJustOnce(com.storytron.uber.Script.NodeTraverser) but works with a NodeTraverser argument.
